    "backText": "**Regions:** Northern Rhône (France — Hermitage, Châteauneuf-du-Pape), Languedoc, California\n**Flavors:** Herbal tea, pear, lime blossom, honey, white flowers\n**Food pairings:** Herb-roasted chicken, risotto, baked fish, soft cheeses\n**Fun fact:** Named for the russet (\"roux\") color of ripe berries. It's notoriously difficult to grow — prone to rot, low yields, and easily oxidized. But when it works, it makes hauntingly aromatic, complex whites that age beautifully.",
