    "deckId": "wine-vocab",
    "frontText": "Brut",
    "backText": "A sweetness level for sparkling wine meaning dry — under 12 g/L residual sugar. The most common Champagne style. The confusing scale: Brut Nature (driest) → Extra Brut → Brut → Extra Dry (sweeter!) → Dry → Demi-Sec → Doux (sweetest).\n\n**Usage:** \"I'll have the brut Champagne — I don't want anything sweet.\"",
    "hint": "Brut = dry bubbles. Extra Dry = actually sweeter. Yes, it's confusing. 🤷",
    "difficulty": 2,
