    "deckId": "wine-vocab",
    "frontText": "Sec",
    "backText": "French for \"dry.\" But on sparkling wine labels, Sec actually means medium-sweet (17-32 g/L sugar). For still wines, sec means dry. For sparkling, the scale is inverted — Brut is drier than Sec.\n\n**Usage:** \"A sec Champagne is actually a bit sweet — if you want truly dry, go brut.\"",
    "hint": "Sec = dry for still wine, but medium-sweet for bubbles. Thanks, France. 🇫🇷",
    "difficulty": 3,
