    "deckId": "wine-vocab",
    "frontText": "Oaky",
    "backText": "Flavors imparted by oak barrel aging: vanilla, toast, caramel, coconut, baking spice, smoke. New oak gives stronger flavors than used (\"neutral\") oak. American oak = bold vanilla/coconut. French oak = subtle spice.\n\n**Usage:** \"This Chardonnay is too oaky for me — all I taste is vanilla and butter.\"",
