    "deckId": "wine-vocab",
    "frontText": "Crisp",
    "backText": "Describes a wine with refreshing, bright acidity — the opposite of soft or flabby. Usually used for white wines. Think of biting into a green apple.\n\n**Usage:** \"I love a crisp Sauvignon Blanc on a hot day — so refreshing.\"",
    "hint": "Green apple snap — fresh, clean, refreshing 🍏",
    "difficulty": 1,
