    "deckId": "wine-vocab",
    "frontText": "Earthy",
    "backText": "Flavors reminiscent of soil, mushrooms, forest floor, damp leaves, or truffles. Common in Old World wines (Burgundy, Barolo). Not a flaw — it's a sign of terroir and complexity.\n\n**Usage:** \"This Burgundy is so earthy — mushrooms and forest floor. Very Old World.\"",
    "hint": "Smells like a walk through the woods after rain 🍂",
