    "frontText": "Jammy",
    "backText": "Describes intensely ripe, cooked-fruit flavors — like smearing jam on toast rather than eating fresh berries. Common in warm-climate reds (Australian Shiraz, California Zin). Can be positive (rich!) or negative (overripe).\n\n**Usage:** \"This Aussie Shiraz is super jammy — blackberry jam with pepper.\"",
